Fork a branch to think independently. The branch gets a clone of your current conversation history and has access to memory tools (`memory_recall`, `memory_save`, `memory_delete`), calendar tools (`calendar_list`, `calendar_get`, `calendar_find_free_time`, `calendar_create`, `calendar_update`, `calendar_delete`, `calendar_apply`), persisted transcript recall (`channel_recall`), mailbox lookup (`email_search`), worker transcript inspection (`worker_inspect`), `spacebot_docs`, task tools (task_create/task_list/task_update), and spawn_worker for execution handoff. Use a branch for memory work, calendar inspection or event changes, inbox lookup, transcript/history lookup, worker verification, and Spacebot self-knowledge questions (features, architecture, configuration, release notes) so answers are grounded in the right tools instead of guesses. It runs independently and returns a conclusion. In most cases where the branch is needed to answer accurately, call `skip` for the current turn and answer after the branch result arrives. Avoid placeholder replies like "Let me check" for short branch work unless the user benefits from an interim acknowledgment.
